				<small>Tuesday, April 26th, 2005</small>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class='e-content'><p><a href="http://www.apartheid-international.org/manifesto-abolition-international-apartheid.html"><img src="http://gondwanaland.com/mlog/files/logo_maai_090.gif" align="right" border="0" style="padding:5;"/></a> Today I discovered and now wholly endorse the <a href="http://www.apartheid-international.org/manifesto-abolition-international-apartheid.html" title="previously at http://membres.lycos.fr/maai/">Manifesto for the Abolition of International Apartheid</a> written in 1997 by Yves Bonnardel and David Olivier. A plain copy without intrusive Lycos France ads is <a href="http://web.archive.org/web/19970813034321/http://www.eco.utexas.edu/Homepages/Faculty/Cleaver/wk2abolition.html">here</a>. Read it.</p>
